title: Wisconsin-Dairyland Programming Competition
text: 2021 was my first programming competition and I enjoyed it thoroughly. I participated for Kettle Moraine High under team "Error: "Team name not found"" we placed third in the blue division (Java) which was the highest position KM had in the six years participating up until that point. I was overjoyed to do it again and while as part of the team "Byte My Bits" in 2022 and while we didn't place in the top, it was nice to particapate in person and see the campus. title: HS Honors Diploma
imageAlt: Kettle Moraine High School KM logo
text: I graduated with an honors diploma from KMHS as part of the class of 2022. During my time at KM I made the honers role every year and was a Dick Ohm recipient all 4 years at the High School. Over my time at KMHS I was on the Robotics Team, the Boys Cross Country team, the Chess club, the ECO club, and the Honors Society. I graduated with a weighted GPA of 4.117 (w/bonus points 4.542).
